
The target is flushed with TCP, UDP and ICMP packets. This is achieved using hping.
Hping is an open-source command-line tool used for crafting and analyzing packets across the TCP/IP protocol. 

INSTALLATION GUIDE:

To install hping, the following steps are performed - 

1. Update package indexes from repositories

      sudo apt update

2. Upgrade any existing packages

      sudo apt upgrade

3. Install hping3

      sudo apt-get install hping3
